Project Overview -
HobbyHub, a website built using Node,js, Javascript, HTML5, EJS templating and CSS3. Allows users to manage hobbies by adding, viewing, editing and deleting hobbies (data entries). The website includes separate pages for displaying all data entries, adding data entries, about the company and contacting the company. 
        Hobbies page
        About page
        Add Hobby Page
        Contact page

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Structure -
The project is organized into separate HTML, EJS, Node.js and JS files for the content contained in the webpage.
       * Node_modules - npm dependencies
       * Public - assets and files available to browsers
           * Assets - media
           * Scripts - client side files
       * Server - data and database files
           * Routes - route handlers
               * Model - data schemas for mongoDB 
               * Config - website and database settings 
               * Views - contains ejs templates 
                   * Hobby - templates for pages
                   * Partials - reusable components 
       * App - express configurations 
       * Server - starts Node server

